{
  "page": "Harvest feast (299)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/ff/Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG/350px-Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/ff/Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG/525px-Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/ff/Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG/700px-Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lino_Drieghe_Winterfell.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> by Lino Drieghe © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>harvest feast</b> is held at <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Besides being a celebration of the harvest, this <a href=\"/index.php/Harvest_feast\" title=\"Harvest feast\">harvest feast</a> allows the <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">bannermen</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> to meet with <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a>, and Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Arrivals\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Arrivals</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Feast\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Feast</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Northern_nobles\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Northern nobles</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#River_nobles\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">River nobles</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Winterfell_household\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Winterfell household</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Other_attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Other attendees</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Arrivals\">Arrivals</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Arrivals\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Stark</a> in Winterfell, <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> hosts the harvest feast of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> brings a large retinue from <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a>, including <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a>, squires, lesser nobility, heralds, musicians, and a juggler; <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Jammos)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Jammos)\">Big Walder</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Merrett)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Merrett)\">Little Walder Frey</a> break lances with the Manderly squires. In contrast to the Manderlys, the widowed Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Donella_Hornwood\" title=\"Donella Hornwood\">Donella Hornwood</a> arrives with only six men-at-arms, and <a href=\"/index.php/Cley_Cerwyn\" title=\"Cley Cerwyn\">Cley Cerwyn</a> brings two dozen lances.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Other nobles who arrive include <a href=\"/index.php/Mors_Umber\" title=\"Mors Umber\">Mors</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Hother_Umber\" title=\"Hother Umber\">Hother Umber</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tallhart\" title=\"House Tallhart\">Tallharts</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Glover_steward\" title=\"Glover steward\">steward</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Deepwood_Motte\" title=\"Deepwood Motte\">Deepwood Motte</a> to represent <a href=\"/index.php/House_Glover\" title=\"House Glover\">House Glover</a>. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ondrew_Locke\" title=\"Ondrew Locke\">Ondrew Locke</a> is too old to make the journey, while Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Lyessa_Flint\" title=\"Lyessa Flint\">Lyessa Flint</a> is pregnant and preoccupied with sickness at <a href=\"/index.php/Widow%27s_Watch\" title=\"Widow&#39;s Watch\">Widow's Watch</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mormont\" title=\"House Mormont\">Mormonts</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Karstark\" title=\"House Karstark\">Karstarks</a> are fighting in the south with <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a>. There is no representative from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bolton\" title=\"House Bolton\">House Bolton</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bran, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a> meet privately with some of the lords in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Keep_(Winterfell)\" title=\"Great Keep (Winterfell)\">Great Keep</a>. Lord Manderly offers to mint <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> and build a fleet for King Robb. Lady Hornwood warns that <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Ramsay Snow</a>, the bastard son of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a>, is gathering men to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dreadfort\" title=\"Dreadfort\">Dreadfort</a>. Rodrik orders the Umbers to work with the Manderlys in building longships to protect against <a href=\"/index.php/Wildling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildling\">wildling</a> incursions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Feast\">Feast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Feast\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hodor_and_Bran_Stark_by_John_Stanko.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5e/Hodor_and_Bran_Stark_by_John_Stanko.png/350px-Hodor_and_Bran_Stark_by_John_Stanko.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"315\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/5/5e/Hodor_and_Bran_Stark_by_John_Stanko.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hodor_and_Bran_Stark_by_John_Stanko.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> by John Stanko © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>At the start of the feast, Bran rides <a href=\"/index.php/Dancer\" title=\"Dancer\">Dancer</a> into the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Hall_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Great Hall of Winterfell\">Great Hall of Winterfell</a> amidst cheers of \"Stark!\" and \"Winterfell!\", and the northmen, both noble and <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Winter_town\" title=\"Winter town\">winter town</a>, celebrate Robb's victories and the harvest. Bran sits at the high table on the dais with Rodrik and his daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Beth_Cassel\" title=\"Beth Cassel\">Beth</a> to his left, and his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon</a> to his right. Also at the high table are Luwin and the Frey wards. Northern lords are given places of honor on the dais as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The food comes from throughout the north and includes <a href=\"/index.php/Aurochs\" title=\"Aurochs\">aurochs</a> roasted with leeks, venison pies, mutton chops, duck, peppered <a href=\"/index.php/Boar\" title=\"Boar\">boar</a>, goose-in-<a href=\"/index.php/Berry\" title=\"Berry\">berries</a>, pigeon, capon, beef-and-barley stew, and cold fruit soup. Seafood from White Harbor includes <a href=\"/index.php/Whitefish\" title=\"Whitefish\">whitefish</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Winkle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Winkle\">winkles</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Crab\" title=\"Crab\">crabs</a>, mussels, clams, <a href=\"/index.php/Herring\" title=\"Herring\">herring</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Cod\" title=\"Cod\">cod</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Salmon\" title=\"Salmon\">salmon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lobster\" title=\"Lobster\">lobster</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Lamprey\" title=\"Lamprey\">lampreys</a>. Additionally, there is black bread, honeycakes, oaten biscuits, turnips, pease, beets, beans, squash, red onions, and wheels of white <a href=\"/index.php/Cheese\" title=\"Cheese\">cheese</a>. Treats include baked apples, berry tarts, and pears poached in <a href=\"/index.php/Strongwine\" title=\"Strongwine\">strongwine</a>. Flagons of hot spice <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> and chilled autumn <a href=\"/index.php/Ale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ale\">ale</a> are served to the guests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Each dish is offered first to Bran, and he offers the most appealing to the nobles, such as salmon to Donella, boar to the Umbers, and goose-in-berries to Cley. To thank <a href=\"/index.php/Joseth\" title=\"Joseth\">Joseth</a> for training Dancer, Bran sends a huge lobster to the <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_horse\" title=\"Master of horse\">master of horse</a>. Bran sends sweets to <a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Nan\" title=\"Old Nan\">Old Nan</a> out of love, and he sends boiled beets to Little Walder and buttered turnips to Big Walder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Songs performed include \"<a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Lances\" title=\"Iron Lances\">Iron Lances</a>\", \"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Burning_of_the_Ships\" title=\"The Burning of the Ships\">The Burning of the Ships</a>\", and \"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Bear_and_the_Maiden_Fair\" title=\"The Bear and the Maiden Fair\">The Bear and the Maiden Fair</a>\". <a href=\"/index.php/Osha\" title=\"Osha\">Osha</a> breaks a flagon over the head of one of <a href=\"/index.php/Leobald_Tallhart\" title=\"Leobald Tallhart\">Leobald Tallhart</a>'s men when he touches her, and <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a> flirts with a woman who welcomes his attention. The Umber brothers play a drinking game involving slamming their horns together.\n</p><p>During the feast, <a href=\"/index.php/Alebelly\" title=\"Alebelly\">Alebelly</a> announces the arrival of <a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jojen_Reed\" title=\"Jojen Reed\">Jojen Reed</a>, who have come in place of their father, <a href=\"/index.php/Howland_Reed\" title=\"Howland Reed\">Howland Reed</a>. Prior to joining the feast, the Reeds reaffirm the <a href=\"/index.php/Crannogmen\" title=\"Crannogmen\">crannogmen</a>'s oath of loyalty to House Stark.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the meal is done, the Great Hall's tables are cleared to make space for dancing. Hother Umber blows a large warhorn during \"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Night_That_Ended\" title=\"The Night That Ended\">The Night That Ended</a>\", while Glover men use <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/bladder_pipe\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:bladder pipe\">bladder</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Harp\" title=\"Harp\">woodharp</a>. Mors Umber begins the dancing by grabbing a serving girl, but he is quickly joined by others. <a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a> dances by himself, while <a href=\"/index.php/Beth_Cassel\" title=\"Beth Cassel\">Beth Cassel</a> dances first with Wyman Manderly and then with Cley Cerwyn.\n</p><p>Unable to dance, the crippled Bran has <a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a> bring him to his bedchamber. En route they see Joseth having sex with a woman in the gallery near the hall. Once back in his room, Bran has Hodor return to the feast. Bran then <a href=\"/index.php/Skinchanger\" title=\"Skinchanger\">dreams</a> of his <a href=\"/index.php/Direwolf\" title=\"Direwolf\">direwolf</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Summer\" title=\"Summer\">Summer</a>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Godswood_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Godswood of Winterfell\">godswood of Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>All of the lords and knights depart Winterfell within a day or two after the feast, though the Reed siblings remain at the castle with Bran.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While returning to <a href=\"/index.php/Hornwood\" title=\"Hornwood\">Hornwood</a>, Lady Hornwood is abducted by Ramsay Snow, leading to <a href=\"/index.php/Fighting_in_the_Hornwood\" title=\"Fighting in the Hornwood\">fighting in the Hornwood</a> between Houses Bolton and Manderly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Northern_nobles\">Northern nobles</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Northern nobles\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\"><img alt=\"House Stark.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/20px-House_Stark.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/30px-House_Stark.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/40px-House_Stark.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\"><img alt=\"House Stark.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/20px-House_Stark.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/30px-House_Stark.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7e/House_Stark.svg/40px-House_Stark.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Cassel\" title=\"House Cassel\"><img alt=\"House Cassel.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/20px-House_Cassel.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/30px-House_Cassel.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/40px-House_Cassel.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Cassel\" title=\"House Cassel\"><img alt=\"House Cassel.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/20px-House_Cassel.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/30px-House_Cassel.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/96/House_Cassel.svg/40px-House_Cassel.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Beth_Cassel\" title=\"Beth Cassel\">Beth Cassel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\"><img alt=\"House Manderly.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/House_Manderly.svg/20px-House_Manderly.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/House_Manderly.svg/30px-House_Manderly.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c9/House_Manderly.svg/40px-House_Manderly.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hornwood\" title=\"House Hornwood\"><img alt=\"House Hornwood.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/03/House_Hornwood.svg/20px-House_Hornwood.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/03/House_Hornwood.svg/30px-House_Hornwood.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/03/House_Hornwood.svg/40px-House_Hornwood.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Donella_Hornwood\" title=\"Donella Hornwood\">Donella Hornwood</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Umber\" title=\"House Umber\"><img alt=\"House Umber.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/20px-House_Umber.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/30px-House_Umber.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/40px-House_Umber.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Mors_Umber\" title=\"Mors Umber\">Mors Umber</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Umber\" title=\"House Umber\"><img alt=\"House Umber.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/20px-House_Umber.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/30px-House_Umber.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/0f/House_Umber.svg/40px-House_Umber.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Hother_Umber\" title=\"Hother Umber\">Hother Umber</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Cerwyn\" title=\"House Cerwyn\"><img alt=\"House Cerwyn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2c/House_Cerwyn.svg/20px-House_Cerwyn.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2c/House_Cerwyn.svg/30px-House_Cerwyn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/2c/House_Cerwyn.svg/40px-House_Cerwyn.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Cley_Cerwyn\" title=\"Cley Cerwyn\">Cley Cerwyn</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tallhart\" title=\"House Tallhart\"><img alt=\"House Tallhart.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/House_Tallhart.svg/20px-House_Tallhart.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/House_Tallhart.svg/30px-House_Tallhart.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fe/House_Tallhart.svg/40px-House_Tallhart.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Leobald_Tallhart\" title=\"Leobald Tallhart\">Leobald Tallhart</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Reed\" title=\"House Reed\"><img alt=\"House Reed.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/20px-House_Reed.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/30px-House_Reed.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/40px-House_Reed.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera Reed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Reed\" title=\"House Reed\"><img alt=\"House Reed.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/20px-House_Reed.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/30px-House_Reed.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b6/House_Reed.svg/40px-House_Reed.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Jojen_Reed\" title=\"Jojen Reed\">Jojen Reed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Glover\" title=\"House Glover\"><img alt=\"House Glover.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/41/House_Glover.svg/20px-House_Glover.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/41/House_Glover.svg/30px-House_Glover.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/41/House_Glover.svg/40px-House_Glover.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Glover_steward\" title=\"Glover steward\">Glover steward</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"River_nobles\">River nobles</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: River nobles\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Jammos)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Jammos)\"><img alt=\"Big Walder Frey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Big_Walder_Frey.svg/20px-Big_Walder_Frey.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Big_Walder_Frey.svg/30px-Big_Walder_Frey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/de/Big_Walder_Frey.svg/40px-Big_Walder_Frey.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Jammos)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Jammos)\">Big Walder Frey</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Merrett)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Merrett)\"><img alt=\"Little Walder Frey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e6/Little_Walder_Frey.svg/20px-Little_Walder_Frey.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e6/Little_Walder_Frey.svg/30px-Little_Walder_Frey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e6/Little_Walder_Frey.svg/40px-Little_Walder_Frey.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Merrett)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Merrett)\">Little Walder Frey</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Winterfell_household\">Winterfell household</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Winterfell household\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Maester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/20px-Maester.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/30px-Maester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/40px-Maester.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Alebelly\" title=\"Alebelly\">Alebelly</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Dancer\" title=\"Dancer\">Dancer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Farlen\" title=\"Farlen\">Farlen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hayhead\" title=\"Hayhead\">Hayhead</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Joseth\" title=\"Joseth\">Joseth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Old_Nan\" title=\"Old Nan\">Old Nan</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Osha\" title=\"Osha\">Osha</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Poxy_Tym\" title=\"Poxy Tym\">Poxy Tym</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Skittrick\" title=\"Skittrick\">Skittrick</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Other_attendees\">Other attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Other attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>smallfolk from the <a href=\"/index.php/Winter_town\" title=\"Winter town\">winter town</a></li>\n<li>friends from nearby <a href=\"/index.php/Holdfast\" title=\"Holdfast\">holdfasts</a></li>\n<li>guards escorting the nobles</li>\n<li>knights, squires, lesser lords and ladies, heralds, musicians, and a juggler, all from <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The feast makes a pleasant pretext, but a man does not cross a hundred leagues for a sliver of duck and a sip of <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>. Only those who have matters of import to set before us are like to make the journey.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He bid them welcome in the name of his brother, the <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a>, and asked them to thank the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_gods\" title=\"Old gods\">gods old</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">new</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb's</a> victories and the bounty of the harvest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Such food Bran had never seen; course after course after course, so much that he could not manage more than a bite or two of each dish.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He looked up and down the benches at all the faces happy and sad, and wondered who would be missing next year and the year after. He might have cried then, but he couldn't. He was the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Stark</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>, his father's son and his brother's heir, and almost a man grown.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harvest_feast_(299)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.8</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of King